Description: A sealing from an unknown object, probably a document, with two oval impressions from intaglio gems, one having facing busts of Zeus-Ammon and of Sarapis, both with a few Greek letters behind their heads, unread, although that behind Sarapis appears to read ']ωN'; the other impression is incomplete and obscure, but includes an ibis standing to right, with perhaps a human head nearby. Unfired pale-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3633)
